Text.SourceString: Are you growing jackfruit, honey? I’d love to have some so I can make minced jackfruit pie.//<portrait=happy>I might bring some over to the Inn for <NPCName>Suki</> as well. She loves them too.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you growing jackfruit, honey? I’d love to have some so I can make minced jackfruit pie.//<portrait=happy>I might bring some over to the Inn for <NPCName>Suki</> as well. She loves them too.

Text.SourceString: I walked around the farm yesterday and the trees looked beautiful on our farm, honey.//<portrait=happy>Great job!//I’m going to miss this when Winter comes along.
Text.LocalizedString: I walked around the farm yesterday and the trees looked beautiful on our farm, honey.//<portrait=happy>Great job!//I’m going to miss this when Winter comes along.

Text.SourceString: Let’s go to the Spooky Festival together this Fall! Let me get my old costume ready.
Text.LocalizedString: Let’s go to the Spooky Festival together this Fall! Let me get my old costume ready.

Text.SourceString: If you see <NPCName>Suki</> today, tell her to keep the heating receipt. And I would call the people.//She would know what you're talking about.
Text.LocalizedString: If you see <NPCName>Suki</> today, tell her to keep the heating receipt. And I would call the people.//She would know what you're talking about.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if <NPCName>Ben</> has left for his trip yet…
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if <NPCName>Ben</> has left for his trip yet…

Text.SourceString: I should head to <NPCName>Ben</> next week. I need to catch him before he leaves for his trip.//I have to pick up some flowers for the inn.
Text.LocalizedString: I should head to <NPCName>Ben</> next week. I need to catch him before he leaves for his trip.//I have to pick up some flowers for the inn.

Text.SourceString: The leaves were crunchy on my walk this morning.
Text.LocalizedString: The leaves were crunchy on my walk this morning.

Text.SourceString: I love walking through the leaves. Do you ever do it?
Text.LocalizedString: I love walking through the leaves. Do you ever do it?

Text.SourceString: I have to start working on a new marketing plan for Winter…
Text.LocalizedString: I have to start working on a new marketing plan for Winter…

Text.SourceString: Why can’t Summer be longer? I haven’t finished my reading yet!
Text.LocalizedString: Why can’t Summer be longer? I haven’t finished my reading yet!

Text.SourceString: It’s the last week of Fall, and do you know what that means?//<portrait=annoyed>We have to prepare the inn for Winter. Ugh.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s the last week of Fall, and do you know what that means?//<portrait=annoyed>We have to prepare the inn for Winter. Ugh.

Text.SourceString: Fall is so pretty, isn’t it? Now, if only it were a bit warmer…
Text.LocalizedString: Fall is so pretty, isn’t it? Now, if only it were a bit warmer…

Text.SourceString: Brrrr. It’s starting to get cold. I’ll have to do my reading inside soon.
Text.LocalizedString: Brrrr. It’s starting to get cold. I’ll have to do my reading inside soon.

Text.SourceString: I miss Summer already…
Text.LocalizedString: I miss Summer already…

Text.SourceString: It’s so chilly…
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so chilly…

Text.SourceString: I wonder if <NPCName>Ben</> has left on his trip yet…
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if <NPCName>Ben</> has left on his trip yet…

Text.SourceString: I should head to <NPCName>Ben</>'s next week. I need to catch him before he leaves for his trip.
Text.LocalizedString: I should head to <NPCName>Ben</>'s next week. I need to catch him before he leaves for his trip.

Text.SourceString: The leaves were crunchy on my walk this morning.
Text.LocalizedString: The leaves were crunchy on my walk this morning.

Text.SourceString: I love walking through the leaves. Do you ever do that?
Text.LocalizedString: I love walking through the leaves. Do you ever do that?

Text.SourceString: I have to start working on a new marketing plan for Winter…
Text.LocalizedString: I have to start working on a new marketing plan for Winter…

Text.SourceString: They give out free mooncakes at the Harvest Festival.//They’re <NPCName>Betty’s</>, so they’re good, for sure!
Text.LocalizedString: They give out free mooncakes at the Harvest Festival.//They’re <NPCName>Betty’s</>, so they’re good, for sure!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Dinda</> and <NPCName>Joko</> are very talented. They made some of cabinets at the inn.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Dinda</> and <NPCName>Joko</> are very talented. They made some of cabinets at the inn.

Text.SourceString: I wonder how long it took them to get so good at carpentry.//<portrait=happy>How long did it take you to get good at farming, honey?
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder how long it took them to get so good at carpentry.//<portrait=happy>How long did it take you to get good at farming, honey?

Text.SourceString: Did you have fun at the New Year’s Eve Party, honey? <NPCName>Bree</> always throws the best party, don’t you think?
Text.LocalizedString: Did you have fun at the New Year’s Eve Party, honey? <NPCName>Bree</> always throws the best party, don’t you think?

Text.SourceString: Hm? Oh yes, it was our birthday, too. <NPCName>Valentina</> gave me a little book she made. Isn't that so precious?
Text.LocalizedString: Hm? Oh yes, it was our birthday, too. <NPCName>Valentina</> gave me a little book she made. Isn't that so precious?

Text.SourceString: Honey, what are you bringing to the potluck? I think I’ll bring some veggies. We can never have too many veggies.
Text.LocalizedString: Honey, what are you bringing to the potluck? I think I’ll bring some veggies. We can never have too many veggies.

Text.SourceString: This time of year, you can find fresh wasabi by the river…
Text.LocalizedString: This time of year, you can find fresh wasabi by the river…

Text.SourceString: Oh, really?//<portrait=normal>Animals might have eaten them already. But have you tried by the river in the forest?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, really?//<portrait=normal>Animals might have eaten them already. But have you tried by the river in the forest?

Text.SourceString: Ah… I kinda miss the snow already.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah… I kinda miss the snow already.

Text.SourceString: On my morning walk the other day, I saw people gathering bamboo shoots near the lake.//We should check it out.
Text.LocalizedString: On my morning walk the other day, I saw people gathering bamboo shoots near the lake.//We should check it out.

Text.SourceString: Are we planning on planting pineapples this Summer, honey?
Text.LocalizedString: Are we planning on planting pineapples this Summer, honey?

Text.SourceString: They’re all right. I was just curious…//But I heard that <NPCName>Joko</> loves pineapples. One time he gave <NPCName>Suki</> and me some as a souvenir from his trip.
Text.LocalizedString: They’re all right. I was just curious…//But I heard that <NPCName>Joko</> loves pineapples. One time he gave <NPCName>Suki</> and me some as a souvenir from his trip.

Text.SourceString: The cherry blossoms look beautiful this time of year.
Text.LocalizedString: The cherry blossoms look beautiful this time of year.

Text.SourceString: This time of year, you can find fresh wasabi by the river…
Text.LocalizedString: This time of year, you can find fresh wasabi by the river…

Text.SourceString: Oh, you didn’t find any, you said?//<portrait=normal>Animals might have eaten them already. But have you tried by the river in the forest?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, you didn’t find any, you said?//<portrait=normal>Animals might have eaten them already. But have you tried by the river in the forest?

Text.SourceString: I’m so happy Spring is almost over, because it means Summer is right around the corner. I love the longer days!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so happy Spring is almost over, because it means Summer is right around the corner. I love the longer days!

Text.SourceString: There’s something cheerful about the flowers in Spring. I know <NPCName>Suki</> can’t get enough of them.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s something cheerful about the flowers in Spring. I know <NPCName>Suki</> can’t get enough of them.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad I made it through another Winter.//<portrait=happy>Now I can look forward to Summer!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad I made it through another Winter.//<portrait=happy>Now I can look forward to Summer!

Text.SourceString: I’m just counting the days until Summer is here, hon.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m just counting the days until Summer is here, hon.

Text.SourceString: I don’t usually love the color pink, but I make an exception for cherry blossoms.//<portrait=happy>They’re just so beautiful.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t usually love the color pink, but I make an exception for cherry blossoms.//<portrait=happy>They’re just so beautiful.

Text.SourceString: Living with <NPCName>Suki</> in Spring has pros and cons.//<portrait=happy>Pro: I barely have to clean anything, because she goes on a cleaning spree.//<portrait=annoyed>Con: She’s even more overbearing and annoying than usual.
Text.LocalizedString: Living with <NPCName>Suki</> in Spring has pros and cons.//<portrait=happy>Pro: I barely have to clean anything, because she goes on a cleaning spree.//<portrait=annoyed>Con: She’s even more overbearing and annoying than usual.

Text.SourceString: There's more bugs here in Summer that at the inn.//We live close to the forest, afterall.
Text.LocalizedString: There's more bugs here in Summer that at the inn.//We live close to the forest, afterall.

Text.SourceString: This is my new favorite reading spot. I love sitting here and seeing our beautiful farm.//<portrait=happy>Oh I love saying that...our farm.
Text.LocalizedString: This is my new favorite reading spot. I love sitting here and seeing our beautiful farm.//<portrait=happy>Oh I love saying that...our farm.

Text.SourceString: What are you growing this season?//Do you need some help deciding?
Text.LocalizedString: What are you growing this season?//Do you need some help deciding?

Text.SourceString: Are you growing jackfruit, honey? I’d love to have some so I can make minced jackfruit pie.//<portrait=happy>I might bring some over to the Inn for <NPCName>Suki</> as well. She loves them too.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you growing jackfruit, honey? I’d love to have some so I can make minced jackfruit pie.//<portrait=happy>I might bring some over to the Inn for <NPCName>Suki</> as well. She loves them too.

Text.SourceString: Make sure you stay warm out there, honey. It’s not too cold, yet, but before you know it, it’s going to get cold.
Text.LocalizedString: Make sure you stay warm out there, honey. It’s not too cold, yet, but before you know it, it’s going to get cold.

Text.SourceString: If I ever leave this town, festivals would be one thing that I’d miss.
Text.LocalizedString: If I ever leave this town, festivals would be one thing that I’d miss.

Text.SourceString: I’m ready for the beach clean-up tomorrow… Don't forget to bring sunscreen, honey.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m ready for the beach clean-up tomorrow… Don't forget to bring sunscreen, honey.

Text.SourceString: Summer, finally! Now I can read outside as much as I want.
Text.LocalizedString: Summer, finally! Now I can read outside as much as I want.

Text.SourceString: Do you know what Summer is good for? Spending time outside, eating tons of minced jackfruit pies, going to the beach – all that good stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know what Summer is good for? Spending time outside, eating tons of minced jackfruit pies, going to the beach – all that good stuff.

Text.SourceString: I’ll read anywhere, but there’s something about reading outside in the Summer sun that’s more relaxing.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll read anywhere, but there’s something about reading outside in the Summer sun that’s more relaxing.

Text.SourceString: Easily the best thing about Summer is the abundance of jackfruit. I can make as many minced jackfruit pies as I want!
Text.LocalizedString: Easily the best thing about Summer is the abundance of jackfruit. I can make as many minced jackfruit pies as I want!

Text.SourceString: I’m excited about the Beach Cleanup Festival later this season. Are you?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m excited about the Beach Cleanup Festival later this season. Are you?

Text.SourceString: It’s easier to do my…research in Summer.//I can stay out longer to see if there’s anything strange on the island.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s easier to do my…research in Summer.//I can stay out longer to see if there’s anything strange on the island.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice to see the community come together. It’s one of the reasons I love the Beach Cleanup Festival.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice to see the community come together. It’s one of the reasons I love the Beach Cleanup Festival.

Text.SourceString: I wish <NPCName>Noah</> would come to the forest with me to help with my research, but he just wants to stay at the beach all day.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish <NPCName>Noah</> would come to the forest with me to help with my research, but he just wants to stay at the beach all day.

Text.SourceString: I love seeing the daisies popping up everywhere. It practically screams Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: I love seeing the daisies popping up everywhere. It practically screams Summer.

Text.SourceString: If I ever leave this town, the festival would be one thing that I’d miss.
Text.LocalizedString: If I ever leave this town, the festival would be one thing that I’d miss.

Text.SourceString: I love seeing all these pretty Summer flowers around the island.//Diversity is beautiful, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: I love seeing all these pretty Summer flowers around the island.//Diversity is beautiful, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: Make sure to use enough sunscreen for the beach cleanup tomorrow, <PlayerName>$player</>. We’ll be in the sun the whole day.
Text.LocalizedString: Make sure to use enough sunscreen for the beach cleanup tomorrow, <PlayerName>$player</>. We’ll be in the sun the whole day.

Text.SourceString: There’s a swimming contest too.//<NPCName>Sunny’s</> going to be the winner again, I bet. Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: There’s a swimming contest too.//<NPCName>Sunny’s</> going to be the winner again, I bet. Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: Ah, the beach looks so clean. But I hope we don’t forget there’s still so much trash in the sea and the river.//We still need to change our lifestyle to stop this from happening.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, the beach looks so clean. But I hope we don’t forget there’s still so much trash in the sea and the river.//We still need to change our lifestyle to stop this from happening.

Text.SourceString: Everyone did such a great job yesterday.
Text.LocalizedString: Everyone did such a great job yesterday.

Text.SourceString: It’ll be <NPCName>Suki</> and my birthday soon. I wonder what <NPCName>Suki</> wants to do this year…
Text.LocalizedString: It’ll be <NPCName>Suki</> and my birthday soon. I wonder what <NPCName>Suki</> wants to do this year…

Text.SourceString: Don’t worry about getting me something for my birthday, honey.//I think you're the best gift...I don't need anything else.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t worry about getting me something for my birthday, honey.//I think you're the best gift...I don't need anything else.

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to another beautiful year with you.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to another beautiful year with you.

Text.SourceString: We got a bad review last year. A couple complained about the heating, so we have to make sure it’s working right this year.//<portrait=sad>It could be bad for business otherwise.
Text.LocalizedString: We got a bad review last year. A couple complained about the heating, so we have to make sure it’s working right this year.//<portrait=sad>It could be bad for business otherwise.

Text.SourceString: When will this Winter be over?
Text.LocalizedString: When will this Winter be over?

Text.SourceString: The only good thing about Winter is it’s when our birthday is.//<portrait=annoyed>Everything else I can do without.
Text.LocalizedString: The only good thing about Winter is it’s when our birthday is.//<portrait=annoyed>Everything else I can do without.

Text.SourceString: I asked my parents <Italic>and</> <NPCName>Suki</> if we could just close the inn for Winter, but they shot me down. Many times.//<portrait=annoyed>You think a broken air conditioner is a problem, wait until you deal with a guest complaining about the heater.
Text.LocalizedString: I asked my parents <Italic>and</> <NPCName>Suki</> if we could just close the inn for Winter, but they shot me down. Many times.//<portrait=annoyed>You think a broken air conditioner is a problem, wait until you deal with a guest complaining about the heater.

Text.SourceString: I’d close the inn all Winter if it were up to me. But we can’t. Something about being the only inn in town. Ugh.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d close the inn all Winter if it were up to me. But we can’t. Something about being the only inn in town. Ugh.

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to the New Year’s Eve Festival. It’s so fun and festive, but it also means Winter is officially over.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to the New Year’s Eve Festival. It’s so fun and festive, but it also means Winter is officially over.

Text.SourceString: It can be a bit of a bummer to have a birthday so close to a festival, but our parents made sure we didn’t feel left out when we were younger.
Text.LocalizedString: It can be a bit of a bummer to have a birthday so close to a festival, but our parents made sure we didn’t feel left out when we were younger.

Text.SourceString: The snow is pretty, I’ll admit. But does it have to be so cold?
Text.LocalizedString: The snow is pretty, I’ll admit. But does it have to be so cold?

Text.SourceString: The inn got a bad review last year. A couple complained about the broken heater in their room. So we have to make sure it’s working this year.//<portrait=sad>It could be bad for business otherwise.
Text.LocalizedString: The inn got a bad review last year. A couple complained about the broken heater in their room. So we have to make sure it’s working this year.//<portrait=sad>It could be bad for business otherwise.

Text.SourceString: I never realized how much I’d love being married. I think it’s because I married my bestfriend.
Text.LocalizedString: I never realized how much I’d love being married. I think it’s because I married my bestfriend.

Text.SourceString: I always wake up with a smile on my face. I blame you for this.
Text.LocalizedString: I always wake up with a smile on my face. I blame you for this.

Text.SourceString: Good thing the inn is so close to the farm. I don’t have to take too long to walk to work.
Text.LocalizedString: Good thing the inn is so close to the farm. I don’t have to take too long to walk to work.

Text.SourceString: Even though I’m not living at the inn anymore, I still want to run it with <NPCName>Suki</>. It is our parents’ legacy, after all.
Text.LocalizedString: Even though I’m not living at the inn anymore, I still want to run it with <NPCName>Suki</>. It is our parents’ legacy, after all.

Text.SourceString: Don’t tell <NPCName>Suki</> this, but I’m glad I’m not living under the same roof as her anymore. I love her, but she can be a bit much, you know?//I need a break from her sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t tell <NPCName>Suki</> this, but I’m glad I’m not living under the same roof as her anymore. I love her, but she can be a bit much, you know?//I need a break from her sometimes.

Text.SourceString: Honey, is everything alright? I feel like I haven’t seen you in ages…
Text.LocalizedString: Honey, is everything alright? I feel like I haven’t seen you in ages…

Text.SourceString: Do you want to spend time with me today? I miss seeing you…
Text.LocalizedString: Do you want to spend time with me today? I miss seeing you…

Text.SourceString: You’ve been very busy lately. You’re not avoiding me, are you?
Text.LocalizedString: You’ve been very busy lately. You’re not avoiding me, are you?

Text.SourceString: I feel like we're driven apart...
Text.LocalizedString: I feel like we're driven apart...

Text.SourceString: Honey, I had some time after my morning walk this morning, so I made you this.
Text.LocalizedString: Honey, I had some time after my morning walk this morning, so I made you this.

Text.SourceString: Honey, I made some minced jackfruit pie for you. Hope it’ll give you enough energy for the day.
Text.LocalizedString: Honey, I made some minced jackfruit pie for you. Hope it’ll give you enough energy for the day.

Text.SourceString: Oh, I have this for you! I forgot to give it to you the other day.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I have this for you! I forgot to give it to you the other day.

Text.SourceString: Oh my goddess, have you seen the meteor that fell outside? The sound of the impact woke me up.//Might be an alien. We never know!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my goddess, have you seen the meteor that fell outside? The sound of the impact woke me up.//Might be an alien. We never know!

Text.SourceString: Hey...um...//I love you, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey...um...//I love you, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: You're an amazing person. Do you know that?
Text.LocalizedString: You're an amazing person. Do you know that?

Text.SourceString: You look good today. I really like that outfit on you.
Text.LocalizedString: You look good today. I really like that outfit on you.

Text.SourceString: It's our wedding anniversary today. I thought I'd spend my day in my wedding dress, reminiscing the happiest day of my life.
Text.LocalizedString: It's our wedding anniversary today. I thought I'd spend my day in my wedding dress, reminiscing the happiest day of my life.

Text.SourceString: I love you, honey.
Text.LocalizedString: I love you, honey.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad I have <NPCName>Suki</>. Is she annoying sometimes? Yes. But I can be annoying too, I’m sure.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad I have <NPCName>Suki</>. Is she annoying sometimes? Yes. But I can be annoying too, I’m sure.

Text.SourceString: Think about it… <NPCName>Suki</> and I have been living together since before we were born. We’re bound to get on each other’s nerves, and squabbles are okay as long as we respect our boundaries.
Text.LocalizedString: Think about it… <NPCName>Suki</> and I have been living together since before we were born. We’re bound to get on each other’s nerves, and squabbles are okay as long as we respect our boundaries.

Text.SourceString: Errr… Be honest with me, have you ever seen anything…weird on our farm?//I don’t know. Maybe…a large masked figure? Why? What did you see?
Text.LocalizedString: Errr… Be honest with me, have you ever seen anything…weird on our farm?//I don’t know. Maybe…a large masked figure? Why? What did you see?

Text.SourceString: Maybe I'll walk around tomorrow. Who knows?! I might run into <Italic>something</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I'll walk around tomorrow. Who knows?! I might run into <Italic>something</>.

Text.SourceString: Do you want to do anything this Sunday? If you want, we could go hiking in the forest and… I don't know.//Camping, maybe?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you want to do anything this Sunday? If you want, we could go hiking in the forest and… I don't know.//Camping, maybe?

Text.SourceString: I feel like I’m talking too much… I am, aren’t I? I’m really not usually like this… I think I’m just comfortable talking to you.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel like I’m talking too much… I am, aren’t I? I’m really not usually like this… I think I’m just comfortable talking to you.

Text.SourceString: I’m okay with the lobster tank at the inn. For all I care, anyone can have whatever pet they want. But I’m not the only one running the inn.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m okay with the lobster tank at the inn. For all I care, anyone can have whatever pet they want. But I’m not the only one running the inn.

Text.SourceString: So how things are around the inn isn’t always up to me.
Text.LocalizedString: So how things are around the inn isn’t always up to me.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Suki</> and I used to have a rescue, but he ended up living in a mansion. I suppose he’s used to living large now.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Suki</> and I used to have a rescue, but he ended up living in a mansion. I suppose he’s used to living large now.

Text.SourceString: It's Taco! He likes to swim at the fountain. He followed <NPCName>Suki</> down from the forest one time and sort of lived here until he decided he liked the vineyard better.
Text.LocalizedString: It's Taco! He likes to swim at the fountain. He followed <NPCName>Suki</> down from the forest one time and sort of lived here until he decided he liked the vineyard better.

Text.SourceString: I don't like pizza. It's alright, I guess...nothing special.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't like pizza. It's alright, I guess...nothing special.

Text.SourceString: I really can’t with <NPCName>Suki</>, sometimes…
Text.LocalizedString: I really can’t with <NPCName>Suki</>, sometimes…

Text.SourceString: She can be so pushy, <PlayerName>$player</>. But don’t worry, I don’t let it bother me anymore.
Text.LocalizedString: She can be so pushy, <PlayerName>$player</>. But don’t worry, I don’t let it bother me anymore.

Text.SourceString: I feel bad, but sometimes I don’t even wanna tell my sis things. I just know that I won’t like her reaction.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel bad, but sometimes I don’t even wanna tell my sis things. I just know that I won’t like her reaction.

Text.SourceString: Like, sometimes I don’t tell her important things… I hate this feeling and having to tiptoe around… I wish I could just tell her everything.
Text.LocalizedString: Like, sometimes I don’t tell her important things… I hate this feeling and having to tiptoe around… I wish I could just tell her everything.

Text.SourceString: I don’t want to hide things from you, <PlayerName>$player</>… And I won’t. You’ve never judged me, and I appreciate that.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t want to hide things from you, <PlayerName>$player</>… And I won’t. You’ve never judged me, and I appreciate that.

Text.SourceString: And let’s face it… Some of the things that I said were… Borderline mean.//A bit harsh, sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: And let’s face it… Some of the things that I said were… Borderline mean.//A bit harsh, sometimes.

Text.SourceString: You’re different, aren’t you? In a good way, I mean.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re different, aren’t you? In a good way, I mean.

Text.SourceString: I’ve never met anybody who knew more about weird phenomena than me… Very impressive, I have to say!
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve never met anybody who knew more about weird phenomena than me… Very impressive, I have to say!

Text.SourceString: I know that I always say how my sister can be hard and stuff, but I don’t know what I would do without her. I don’t think I’d have survived grade school, to tell you the truth.
Text.LocalizedString: I know that I always say how my sister can be hard and stuff, but I don’t know what I would do without her. I don’t think I’d have survived grade school, to tell you the truth.

Text.SourceString: I can't believe I'm married to you.//I'm so happy... I don't think my heart can contain it.
Text.LocalizedString: I can't believe I'm married to you.//I'm so happy... I don't think my heart can contain it.

Text.SourceString: I'M A WIFE!!! OH MY GOSH!!!
Text.LocalizedString: I'M A WIFE!!! OH MY GOSH!!!

Text.SourceString: We should watch TV tonight...just do nothing and watch TV until late.
Text.LocalizedString: We should watch TV tonight...just do nothing and watch TV until late.

Text.SourceString: After all these time, saying that this is our home still gives me butterfly.//It feels good to have something to share with you...something that belongs to just the two of us.
Text.LocalizedString: After all these time, saying that this is our home still gives me butterfly.//It feels good to have something to share with you...something that belongs to just the two of us.

Text.SourceString: I saw a satellite had fallen on our farm outside! I hope nothing major was destroyed…
Text.LocalizedString: I saw a satellite had fallen on our farm outside! I hope nothing major was destroyed…

Text.SourceString: It's so nice here.
Text.LocalizedString: It's so nice here.

Text.SourceString: Why don’t we have a picnic here soon? We can make a few things...sit under a tree, what do you say?
Text.LocalizedString: Why don’t we have a picnic here soon? We can make a few things...sit under a tree, what do you say?

Text.SourceString: It's so quiet here in the morning.//<portrait=happy>Well, quiet compared to the inn, that is. I hear all sorts of animals. It's really nice.
Text.LocalizedString: It's so quiet here in the morning.//<portrait=happy>Well, quiet compared to the inn, that is. I hear all sorts of animals. It's really nice.

Text.SourceString: Morning, honey. It’s really nice to wake up next to you.//<portrait=normal>I don't think I'll ever get tired of it.
Text.LocalizedString: Morning, honey. It’s really nice to wake up next to you.//<portrait=normal>I don't think I'll ever get tired of it.

Text.SourceString: You smell nice.
Text.LocalizedString: You smell nice.

Text.SourceString: It feels weird not to sleep here anymore. I’ve lived here most of my life.//When I’m done with work here, I’ll come back home to you instead of walking a few steps to my room. It’s weird, but I love it.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels weird not to sleep here anymore. I’ve lived here most of my life.//When I’m done with work here, I’ll come back home to you instead of walking a few steps to my room. It’s weird, but I love it.

Text.SourceString: What time is it? It feels so late.
Text.LocalizedString: What time is it? It feels so late.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice to have some peace and quiet after a long day here. When I was living in the inn, there were always people everywhere.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice to have some peace and quiet after a long day here. When I was living in the inn, there were always people everywhere.

Text.SourceString: How was your day? You look a bit tired.//<portrait=normal>Let's rest soon, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: How was your day? You look a bit tired.//<portrait=normal>Let's rest soon, okay?

Text.SourceString: What should we cook tonight? I'm thinking some spicy food.//<portrait=normal>Let me see if we had the ingredients for red curry.
Text.LocalizedString: What should we cook tonight? I'm thinking some spicy food.//<portrait=normal>Let me see if we had the ingredients for red curry.

Text.SourceString: I had a dream about you last night.//No, not a nightmare. Ha ha… It was a good dream.
Text.LocalizedString: I had a dream about you last night.//No, not a nightmare. Ha ha… It was a good dream.

Text.SourceString: Are you going to give me a kiss?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you going to give me a kiss?

Text.SourceString: Don't work so hard today, okay?//<portrait=sad>I don't want you to get sick.
Text.LocalizedString: Don't work so hard today, okay?//<portrait=sad>I don't want you to get sick.

Text.SourceString: It feels weird not to sleep here anymore since I’ve lived here most of my life.//<portrait=happy>When I’m done with work here, I’ll come back home to you. It’s weird, but I love it.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels weird not to sleep here anymore since I’ve lived here most of my life.//<portrait=happy>When I’m done with work here, I’ll come back home to you. It’s weird, but I love it.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Suki</> could never run this inn alone. This isn’t a slight on her, I can’t either!//The inn is just too big for someone to manage alone.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Suki</> could never run this inn alone. This isn’t a slight on her, I can’t either!//The inn is just too big for someone to manage alone.

Text.SourceString: I have to make sure we do the books properly. I might need to bring some of the documents home.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to make sure we do the books properly. I might need to bring some of the documents home.

Text.SourceString: I made some snacks for <NPCName>Valentina</> earlier.//They're in the fridge.
Text.LocalizedString: I made some snacks for <NPCName>Valentina</> earlier.//They're in the fridge.

Text.SourceString: Find anything interesting to read, honey? There’s plenty here.//<portrait=concerned>I wish I could just take it all over to our house.
Text.LocalizedString: Find anything interesting to read, honey? There’s plenty here.//<portrait=concerned>I wish I could just take it all over to our house.

Text.SourceString: I have to wrap up work for the week and make sure everything’s ready for <NPCName>Suki</> tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to wrap up work for the week and make sure everything’s ready for <NPCName>Suki</> tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: She hates it if everything’s not just right. I suppose that’s good, though.
Text.LocalizedString: She hates it if everything’s not just right. I suppose that’s good, though.

Text.SourceString: *<NPCName>Alice</> seems to be working*
Text.LocalizedString: *<NPCName>Alice</> seems to be working*

Text.SourceString: I just updated our point-of-sale system. Let’s see how it works!
Text.LocalizedString: I just updated our point-of-sale system. Let’s see how it works!

Text.SourceString: Hmm, so sleepy… Maybe I should take a nap. Wanna join me, honey?
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm, so sleepy… Maybe I should take a nap. Wanna join me, honey?

Text.SourceString: Be careful out there, okay? Maybe we can snuggle under the blanket tonight with a hot cup of tea.
Text.LocalizedString: Be careful out there, okay? Maybe we can snuggle under the blanket tonight with a hot cup of tea.

Text.SourceString: Our house will be alright, right? This storm seems angry.
Text.LocalizedString: Our house will be alright, right? This storm seems angry.

Text.SourceString: I just saw a squirrel playing in the snow by our house today. It was so adorable!
Text.LocalizedString: I just saw a squirrel playing in the snow by our house today. It was so adorable!

Text.SourceString: What if I just stay at home all day instead of going outside? Sigh, but I miss <NPCName>Valentina</>…//<portrait=sad>And my sister...
Text.LocalizedString: What if I just stay at home all day instead of going outside? Sigh, but I miss <NPCName>Valentina</>…//<portrait=sad>And my sister...

Text.SourceString: Oh gosh, I hope the inn is doing alright. Maybe I should stay over tonight in case there’s an emergency.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh gosh, I hope the inn is doing alright. Maybe I should stay over tonight in case there’s an emergency.

Text.SourceString: Oh gosh, I hope the inn is doing alright. Maybe I should stay over tonight in case there’s an emergency.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh gosh, I hope the inn is doing alright. Maybe I should stay over tonight in case there’s an emergency.

Text.SourceString: Hmm, so sleepy… Maybe I should take a nap.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm, so sleepy… Maybe I should take a nap.

Text.SourceString: It’s so gloomy outside… But at least you get to have a break, right?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so gloomy outside… But at least you get to have a break, right?

Text.SourceString: What a bummer. Looks like I won’t be able to look at the stars tonight.
Text.LocalizedString: What a bummer. Looks like I won’t be able to look at the stars tonight.

Text.SourceString: I think tonight will be a good night to stargaze at home. The sky looks very clear. Maybe you can join me.
Text.LocalizedString: I think tonight will be a good night to stargaze at home. The sky looks very clear. Maybe you can join me.

Text.SourceString: I love when it’s so sunny outside.//The sun feels great on my skin.
Text.LocalizedString: I love when it’s so sunny outside.//The sun feels great on my skin.

Text.SourceString: What a beautiful day. Hey, why don’t we go out and do something together? Maybe a picnic at the beach?
Text.LocalizedString: What a beautiful day. Hey, why don’t we go out and do something together? Maybe a picnic at the beach?

Text.SourceString: Gosh, it’s too cold! Do you maybe wanna cuddle and help me warm up?
Text.LocalizedString: Gosh, it’s too cold! Do you maybe wanna cuddle and help me warm up?

Text.SourceString: Let’s cuddle and watch something tonight. I need help warming up.
Text.LocalizedString: Let’s cuddle and watch something tonight. I need help warming up.

Text.SourceString: What a bummer. Looks like I won’t be able to look at the stars tonight.
Text.LocalizedString: What a bummer. Looks like I won’t be able to look at the stars tonight.

Text.SourceString: Meh… A little rain is fine with me…
Text.LocalizedString: Meh… A little rain is fine with me…

Text.SourceString: I see you don’t mind it either…
Text.LocalizedString: I see you don’t mind it either…

Text.SourceString: *<NPCName>Alice</> is ignoring you*
Text.LocalizedString: *<NPCName>Alice</> is ignoring you*

Text.SourceString: I know how much you appreciate good food, so I prepared this dish for you.//Bon appétit, honey.
Text.LocalizedString: I know how much you appreciate good food, so I prepared this dish for you.//Bon appétit, honey.

Text.SourceString: I've been experimenting in the kitchen, and I made you this.//I hope you enjoy it, honey.
Text.LocalizedString: I've been experimenting in the kitchen, and I made you this.//I hope you enjoy it, honey.

Text.SourceString: I still can't believe we're officially married. It feels like a dream come true. //I'M A WIFE!
Text.LocalizedString: I still can't believe we're officially married. It feels like a dream come true. //I'M A WIFE!
